### 🔍 Before redriving, always read the message to understand what failed and why:
aws sqs receive-message \
  --queue-url https://sqs.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/578761488692/text-processing-queue-DLQ \
  --region eu-west-1 \
  --max-number-of-messages 10

#### *Then check CloudWatch logs for the error that caused it to fail*
aws logs tail /aws/lambda/TextProcessingFonction \
  --region eu-west-1

### 🛠️ Fix the Root Cause
### Test the Fix First
#### *Always test with a fresh upload before redriving to confirm your fix works:*

# Upload a new test file
echo "this is a test file" > test.txt
aws s3 cp test.txt s3://eyong-file-upload-bucket/ --region eu-west-1

- Check CloudWatch logs to confirm it processed successfully. Only then move to redriving.

### Redrive Only After Fix is Confirmed
- Via Console:
1. Go to SQS → text-processing-queue-DLQ
2. Click Start DLQ redrive
3. Select Redrive to source queue
4. Click Start

- Via CLI:

 aws sqs start-message-move-task \
  --source-arn arn:aws:sqs:eu-west-1:578761488692:text-processing-queue-DLQ \
  --region eu-west-1
